description.narrative: This Restructuring Paper entails modification of some of the project development outcome (PDO) indicators and Disbursement Linked Indicators (DLIs) for the IN: PMGSY Rural Roads Project. The need for the proposed restructuring emerged during discussions that took place during the Mid Term Review (MTR) mission in February 2014 wherein the Bank along with NRRDA and participating states undertook a detailed review of each of the DLIs and proposed changes to them for the following reasons: (i) downward revision in credit/loan size from US$ 1,500 million to US$ 1,400 million which impacts the amount allocated to component A; (ii) inclusion of the eighth state of Bihar to the project portfolio; (iii) ensuring consistency between the Financing Agreement and the PAD for the DLIs; and (iv) aligning the DLIs better with the final outcome indicators, and making those more pragmatic in light of current achievements and likelihood of achieving the targets. The mission also reviewed the PDO level results indicators for their continued relevance and achievability, and proposed to modify two of the outcome indicators. It is envisaged that the proposed restructuring of the DLIs and PDO level results indicators would enable the participating states to meet the PDO in a more meaningful manner within the scheduled project period. Restructuring of the PDO indicators entails: (i) dropping the indicator related to travel time as a large majority of habitations being connected under this project had no vehicular access previously and a comparison of travel time between motorized and non- motorized means of travel could be quite misleading; and (ii) modifying the indicator related to access from share of population to share of habitations in order to better align with the program’s core objective of habitation connectivity and also to address lack of data due to decadal frequency of populatio
